If working in PHP, make sure to use lots of variable variables (<a href="https://php.net/manual/en/language.variables.variable.php" rel="nofollow">https://php.net/manual/en/language.variables.variable.php</a>).<p><pre><code>  $a = &#x27;cat&#x27;;
  $$a = &#x27;hello&#x27;;

  echo &quot;$a&quot;; // &quot;cat&quot;
  echo &quot;$cat&quot;; // &quot;hello&quot;;</code></pre>

I&#x27;ve been using Vultr with FreeBSD10 for over 6 months now.
During that time, I had to upgrade my machine to a larger one.
After seeing it as reliable, stable and zero downtime, I now use it as a production machine.<p>So far, I&#x27;ve had no issues and the prices are reasonable, compared to &quot;rootbsd&quot;
